class Solution {
public:
    int sumOfPower(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        int n = nums.size();
        vector<vector<long long>> dp(n + 1, vector<long long>(k + 1, 0));
        dp[0][0] = 1;
        for (int pos = 1; pos <= n; pos++) {
            for (int len = pos; len >= 1; len--) {
                for (int sum = nums[pos - 1]; sum <= k; sum++) {
                    dp[len][sum] = (dp[len][sum] + dp[len - 1][sum - nums[pos - 1]]);
                }
            }
        }
        long long ans = 0;
        for (int len = 1; len <= n; len++) {
            ans = (ans + dp[len][k] * power(2, n - len));
        }
        return ans;
    }
    const int mod = 1e9 + 7;

    long long power(long long a, long long b) {
        long long res = 1;
        while (b) {
            if (b & 1)
                res = (res * a) % mod;
            a = (a * a) % mod;
            b >>= 1;
        }
        return res;
    }
};

/* 
The code snippet uses a dynamic programming algorithm to solve the problem.
It first initializes a 2-D vector dp, with a dp[i][j] to keep the number of 
ways to partition a set of i numbers into at most j groups.
The algorithm will first consider the size of each group is smaller than half 
of the total numbers, that is, group sizes in [1, n / 2].
It then iterates over each number in the input set, that is, [nums[0], 
nums[1], ‚Ä¶, nums[n-1]]. For each number, it first iterates over each group 
size in dp, that is, dp[len][sum], which stores the number of ways to 
partition a set of numbers into len groups with a total sum of sum.
For each group size sum and number number, 
the algorithm will add (dp[len - 1][sum - number] + dp[len][sum - number - 1]) 
to dp[len][sum]. This is because in the original problem, the number number 
is in the group sum, and there are len - 1 groups left. To find the remaining 
number of ways, the algorithm will first consider dp[len - 1][sum - number], 
which is the number of ways to partition a set of numbers into len - 1 groups 
with a total sum of sum - number, and then add (dp[len - 1][sum - number] + dp[len - 1][sum - number - 1]) 
to dp[len][sum], which is the number of ways to partition a set of numbers into 
len groups with a total sum of sum. 
Then the algorithm will consider group size sum + number in dp, which is the 
number of ways to partition a set of numbers into len groups with a total sum of 
sum + number. In addition to this, the algorithm will add dp[len][sum + number] 
to dp[len][sum], which is the number of ways to partition a set of numbers into 
len groups with a total sum of sum + number. This is because in the original 
problem, the number number is in the group sum + number, and there are 
